This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image classification accuracy and latency constraints on mobile devices. It also involves the design of Convolutional Networks (ConvNets) which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

It could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a novel differentiable Neural Architecture Search (NAS) method for designing device-efficient ConvNets. 

The paper also involves Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with the automatic design of ConvNets. 

Neural Networks (cs.NE) is another likely sub-category as the paper involves the design of a single-path, over-parameterized ConvNet to encode all architectural decisions with shared convolutional kernel parameters. 

Finally, the paper could also belong to the Augmented Reality (cs.AR) sub-category as it involves the design of ConvNets for on-device image classification, which is a common task in augmented reality applications.
